/*
:name: mod_cycle_range
:type: error
:tolg: 1
:error: lands at cycle\(s\) \(0,0\) but \(1,2\) is declared at the interface
*/

// A closed landing-cycle RANGE on a mod output is LEGAL (multi-path values,
// see equiv/mod_twopaths) — but it is still CHECKED: a combinational
// feedthrough computes (0,0), which the declared (1,2) interval rejects.
mod f(a:u8) -> (x:u8@[1..=2]) { x = a }
